replies.bodyText:
I think the other test case was not sufficient. Eg the following fails, the complexity of the switch expr is not counted:
class Foo {
    int bar() { return 1; }
    void foo(int i) {                    // +1
        int x = switch (i) {
            case 1, 2, 3 -> bar();  // +3
            case 4       -> bar();  // +1
            default -> bar();
        };
    }
}
I'll push a fix
